msDesc.head: Regula salvatoris and texts concerning St Birgitta

supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil. manum quando manualia
supportDesc.condition: A few larger holes and wormholes.

p.note:
Top left corner in pencil by a modern hand: 97 S. Brigittae ; centre page: the medieval book plate of Hilprand Brandenburg; below in pencil by a modern hand: Ex libris Hildebrani floruit 1500 - F
; below: modern stamp of National Library; bottom left corner: National Library book label with current signum; bottom right corner in pencil: H 2; below in blue ink: the year of accession and accession number, 1944/14.
Top left corner: a glued-on paper label, torn, but with the number 3 legible.

binding.p: Medieval binding. Grayish white leather over bevelled wooden boards. 3 double raised bands and 2 endbands. 1 hooked clasp. : a paper label, in brown ink, Regula S. Salvatoris Offic. et Legenda S. Brigitte Vidue; below, stamped in gold: A 75a; below: the remains of another paper label; , top: traces of writing in brown ink, barely legible [Regula Sancti Salvatoris?]; bottom, in pencil: 378[3?].
binding.decoNote: and , blind tooled triple-line borders; within, a blind tooled pattern of lozenges; at each intersection of the diagonal lines, a blind stamped flower; at the centre of each lozenge (or triangle), a blind stamped fleur-de-lis in a double-line lozenge-shaped frame, or a blind stamped upside down acorn.
binding.condition: Leather somewhat worn; in a few places, wormholes which have penetrated the wooden boards. Clasp and strap missing.

history.origin: Germany Maihingen , 15th century, last quarter, see colophon on .

msItem.title: Regula salvatoris (The Birgittine Rule, the third-person version)
msItem.rubric: Incipit regula Sancti Saluatoris a sede apostolica pro constitutionibus approbata et confirmata de humilitate castitate et paupertate Capitulum primum
msItem.incipit: Principium itaque huius religionis et salutis
msItem.explicit: quod terra sunt et in terram reuertentur
msItem.finalRubric: Explicit regula sanctissima domini nostri Ihesu christi Saluatoris
msItem.note: The text corresponds the the sigma version edited by Eklund, excluding, however, the bull of Urban VI.

msItem.title: Revelations regarding the Birgittine rule
msItem.rubric: Secuntur aliquae reuelationes sy super regulam et statuta pertinentes et primo de organis non habendis in monasteryo
msItem.incipit: Cristus loquitur sancte Birgitte fily israel quia carnales erant
msItem.explicit: in duabus septimanis si expedit saluti et cetera
msItem.note: The section contains chapter X, XIII, XIV, XV and XXIII of the Revelationes extravagantes.

msItem.title: Office for St Birgitta
msItem.rubric: Sequitur historia de sancta Birgitta matris nostre de eius veneracione In i vesperis antiphone super psalmos feriales
msItem.explicit: et recte viuendi nobis operentur effectum per dominum etc
msItem.note:
A detailed inventory of the contents of the office is given by Collijn (1945)
; the office ends with a mass for the commemoration of St Birgitta ().

msItem.title: Office for St Birgitta
Office with mass
msItem.rubric: Incipit hystoria in solemnitatibus Sancte Birgitte de regno Suecie antiphona in primis vesperis psalmus
msItem.incipit: Omnia laudate Birgitte matris inclite festa iocunda suscipe
msItem.explicit: oratio in cuius veneratione hec tue obtulimus maiestati per dominum nostrum etc
msItem.note:
A detailed inventory of the contents of the office is given by Collijn (1945)
; the office ends with a mass for the commemoration of St Birgitta ( ).

msItem.title: Life of St Birgitta
msItem.explicit: eam venerandam declarat et mirificat dominus noster Ihesus christus qui est benedictus in secula seculorum Amen
msItem.finalRubric: Explicit hystoria cum legenda sancte Birgitte de regno suecie compilata per venerabilem patrem dominum Birgerum Archiepiscopum Upsalensem scripta in monasteryo Marie mayhingen ordinis sancti Saluatoris Et est sciendum quod ter in anno habetur festum de eadem sancta Birgitta videlicet Natale quando scilicet defuncta est quod cadit in proxima die post festum sancte marie magdalene que est x kalendas augusti secundum eius festum est translacione quando scilicet translata est de roma ad partes Suecie quod cadit xxviii die mensis May tertium vero eius festum est canonizacionis quod cadit iiii die mensis octobris etc

msItem.title: Canonization bull of Boniface IX
msItem.rubric: Sequitur bulla canonizacionis Sancte Birgitte matris nostre
msItem.incipit: Bonifacius IX episcopus seruus seruorum dei venerabilibus fratribus
msItem.explicit: gaudia peruenire Datum rome aput sanctum Petrum nonis octobris pontificatus nostri anno secundo

supportDesc.condition: A few wormholes in places. Upper outer corner of textblock affected by water damage throughout, but text unaffected.

p.note: In light brown ink by an early modern hand: Cartusianorum in Buxheim; outer margin in the same ink: a ringed cross.
Occasional marginal notations; several passages highlighted by a red line along outer margin with or without an accompanying nota-mark (e.g. ); : manicule.
Modern stamp of the National Library.

Note in pencil in a modern hand: Bokägaremärket: Hildebrand Brandenburg: från Biberach (Würtemberg) Cartusianermunk i klostret Buxheim vid Memingen Det äldsta kända tyska ex libris (tiden omkr. 1470).

decoDesc.p: Main text in brown ink; capitals touched in red; chapter rubrics in red.
decoDesc.decoNote: Plain opening initial P over 6 lines in red with interior reserved spaces; plain cross in counter-space in a different ink. Plain initials over 2-3 lines in red with some penwork. Plain initials over 1 line in red.
